Use m4 macros to ease creation of html slides. Slide
code taken from Google ( http://code.google.com/p/html5slides/ ),
see AUTHORS and LICENSE for more information.

Copy test directory to a new dir. Modify Makefile to build
this directory, and optionally change the TEST target to 
point to new dir. Use 'make' to build, or 'make run' to
build and view in browser. Tested on OSX and Linux.

$ cp -a test mypresentation
$ git add mypresentation
$ # edit mypresentation, add mypresentation to Makefile
$ git commit -am 'Update'
$ make run

Amit Bakshi
12/04/2012
